  <h2>Research Interests</h2>
  
  <p>My broad research interests lie in the areas of <strong>Software Engineering</strong>, <strong>Programming Systems</strong>, <strong>Databases</strong>, and <strong>Distributed Systems</strong>, as well as the integration of <strong>Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning</strong> into Software Engineering practices.</p>
  
  <p>I'm particularly interested in exploring how we can design and build intelligent, reliable, and adaptive software systems — systems that can monitor, reason about, and improve their own performance and behavior over time.</p>

  <p>Some questions that fascinate me include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>How can we make large-scale software systems more self-managing and resilient?</li>
    <li>How can data-driven methods assist developers in debugging, testing, and maintaining complex systems?</li>
    <li>What programming abstractions or tools can simplify the design of distributed and intelligent applications?</li>
  </ul>

  <p>I'm passionate about research that bridges theory and practice — combining solid engineering principles with modern data-driven or intelligent techniques to create more autonomous and dependable software systems.</p>
